query:
In the books database, each order line can have a set of details stored in a JSON column named 'line_details' within the 'order_line' table. Each detail object contains an 'edition_id' and an 'in_stock' status indicating whether that specific edition is available. For example, a single record might look like this:
{"edition_id": 1, "in_stock": true}
For each order line, extract all detail objects from the JSON array, count the total number of details, and count how many of those details have 'in_stock' set to 1 (true).

issue_sql:
DO $$
DECLARE 
    v_rental_id INTEGER;
    v_rental_date BYTEA;
    v_film_title TEXT;
    v_customer_first_name TEXT;
    v_customer_last_name TEXT;
    v_staff_first_name TEXT;
    v_staff_last_name TEXT;
BEGIN
    SELECT
        r.rental_id,
        r.rental_date,
        f.title,
        c.first_name,
        c.last_name,
        s.first_name,
        s.last_name
    FROM rental AS r
    JOIN inventory AS i ON r.inventory_id = i.inventory_id
    JOIN film AS f ON i.film_id = f.film_id
    JOIN customer AS c ON r.customer_id = c.customer_id
    JOIN staff AS s ON r.staff_id = s.staff_id
    ORDER BY r.rental_date;
END $$

